00:15:44,377 --> 00:15:47,779
Since meeting me, you've jumped ship
from a comfortable career

246
00:15:47,880 --> 00:15:51,339
because you decided that you
were missing something. And...

247
00:15:53,286 --> 00:15:57,690
you asked a complete stranger
to marry you.

248
00:15:59,625 --> 00:16:01,321
Who knows what's next?

249
00:16:02,295 --> 00:16:04,491
I guess you'll have to keep thinking.

250
00:16:19,078 --> 00:16:21,070
Dr. Browne, widen the debridement.

251
00:16:21,247 --> 00:16:24,012
Extending the incisions
proximally.

252
00:16:24,083 --> 00:16:26,211
Her husband thought she was a rock.

253
00:16:26,319 --> 00:16:28,845
Turns out she's a rock
because nothing matters to her.

254
00:16:29,055 --> 00:16:30,785
You're making assumptions.

255
00:16:30,857 --> 00:16:34,919
We were monitoring her reaction to pain.
Love wasn't part of the test.

256
00:16:35,027 --> 00:16:37,690
- You care, you hurt.
- Maybe not Lily.

257
00:16:38,331 --> 00:16:41,768
She married this man,
she stayed with him for years.

258
00:16:41,868 --> 00:16:46,238
Maybe for her, love can exist
without the pain of loss.

259
00:16:47,173 --> 00:16:48,869
That would be paradise.

260
00:16:52,612 --> 00:16:56,515
There is way more necrotic tissue
here than I expected.

261
00:16:57,917 --> 00:16:59,545
She's gonna lose the hand.

262
00:17:05,691 --> 00:17:07,785
If anyone can handle bad news...

263
00:17:15,835 --> 00:17:19,738
- Are you going to take my hand?
- Not right now, no.

264
00:17:22,575 --> 00:17:25,067
I don't like to hold hands.

265
00:17:27,413 --> 00:17:31,646
Either we hold hands, or we don't.

266
00:17:31,784 --> 00:17:34,583
There's no compromise.

267
00:17:35,121 --> 00:17:37,113
Only one of us can get
what they want.

268
00:17:37,857 --> 00:17:40,349
- I guess that's true...
- It should be me.

269
00:17:40,426 --> 00:17:43,590
Holding hands makes me uncomfortable.

270
00:17:43,663 --> 00:17:46,929
Not holding hands
doesn't make you uncomfortable.

271
00:18:00,146 --> 00:18:05,244
That show we watched the other night.
It had a happy ending...

272
00:18:06,485 --> 00:18:09,478
because they stopped
the story in a good place.

273
00:18:10,456 --> 00:18:15,087
But in real life, it's gonna get dark
and cold out there.

274
00:18:16,762 --> 00:18:18,094
All we have...

275
00:18:19,165 --> 00:18:20,189
is this.

276
00:18:21,667 --> 00:18:26,901
This says we're in it together,
we've got each other's back.

277
00:18:28,674 --> 00:18:31,701
That we'll hold each other up
for as long as we can.

278
00:18:34,313 --> 00:18:38,808
I can say all those things verbally.

279
00:18:38,918 --> 00:18:43,185
You could shout them,
and it wouldn't say it as loud as this.

280
00:18:46,158 --> 00:18:50,619
You said not holding hands wouldn't
make me uncomfortable, but it would.

281
00:18:53,432 --> 00:18:54,661
I would feel...

282
00:18:57,536 --> 00:18:58,560
separate.

283
00:19:33,973 --> 00:19:34,973
It's all right.

284
00:19:48,020 --> 00:19:51,548
You've actually been lucky,
considering you have no warning system.

285
00:19:51,624 --> 00:19:55,686
You need to be doing self-checks.
Knees, feet, elbows, hands.

286
00:19:56,028 --> 00:19:58,020
Look for bruises, discolorations,

287
00:19:58,097 --> 00:20:02,432
anything at all that changes
could be dangerous, life-threatening.

288
00:20:03,069 --> 00:20:06,972
But there's another option. Naloxone
affects the central nervous system.

289
00:20:07,073 --> 00:20:10,134
It's been shown to block the action
of pain-lowering endorphins.

290
00:20:10,242 --> 00:20:12,541
It could give you the ability
to feel pain.

291
00:20:12,611 --> 00:20:14,910
I don't see the point,
I've been fine so far.

292
00:20:15,514 --> 00:20:18,541
Guess that sounds silly,
I just lost a hand.

293
00:20:18,617 --> 00:20:23,112
But now I know about checking myself,
and I'll be a lot more careful.

294
00:20:36,235 --> 00:20:39,034
Why is one gesture so important?

295
00:20:40,840 --> 00:20:43,605
- Carly still pushing you to hold hands?
- No.

296
00:20:43,676 --> 00:20:47,579
I tried, and she said it was all right.

297
00:20:47,646 --> 00:20:48,739
Huh.

298
00:20:50,916 --> 00:20:54,512
You should give me context
for that "huh."

299
00:20:56,122 --> 00:20:58,489
She wants it, she's just given up.

300
00:20:59,592 --> 00:21:00,491
Good.

301
00:21:00,593 --> 00:21:04,121
Not if it's gonna bother her
the rest of your relationship,

302
00:21:04,196 --> 00:21:06,256
which may not be very long.

303
00:21:09,435 --> 00:21:10,435
Huh.

304
00:21:15,608 --> 00:21:16,608
Uh-oh.

305
00:21:20,346 --> 00:21:22,791
We need to do imaging to make sure
the problem isn't the shunt.

306
00:21:22,815 --> 00:21:24,511
Check there isn't a clot
causing backup...

307
00:21:24,617 --> 00:21:27,018
The surgery was a success,
but I'm still being poisoned?

308
00:21:27,119 --> 00:21:31,318
No. The surgery was a success,
but your liver's still deteriorating.

309
00:21:31,390 --> 00:21:32,390
We don't know why.

310
00:21:35,361 --> 00:21:37,023
Jen, check me out.
Find another hospital.

311
00:21:37,129 --> 00:21:39,291
I can't approve that.
You're in no condition to leave.

312
00:21:39,365 --> 00:21:41,977
You've just confirmed that someone
in this hospital is poisoning me.

313
00:21:42,001 --> 00:21:43,970
You want me to cooperate
with the suspects?

314
00:21:44,036 --> 00:21:46,801
Another hospital
wouldn't solve your problem.

315
00:21:47,706 --> 00:21:50,801
People can be gotten to,

316
00:21:50,876 --> 00:21:52,902
bribed, or threatened.

317
00:21:56,916 --> 00:21:59,511
- Right. Someone here wants to kill me.
- No one is trying...

318
00:21:59,618 --> 00:22:03,316
Let's constrain some of these variables.
One person touches me.

319
00:22:04,056 --> 00:22:05,183
Him.

320
00:22:05,558 --> 00:22:09,427
- He doesn't know how to lie.
- I can lie.

321
00:22:09,528 --> 00:22:11,520
Yes, but not successfully.
Good choice.

322
00:22:18,204 --> 00:22:21,697
- Will I be able to play tennis?
- Yes, eventually.

323
00:22:21,907 --> 00:22:23,671
Funny, I never could before.

324
00:22:26,412 --> 00:22:28,438
You always take things well.

325
00:22:30,216 --> 00:22:32,242
We had to pick up
and move from Durham.

326
00:22:32,351 --> 00:22:36,413
Well, that was for your job.
No sense in moping about it.

327
00:22:37,957 --> 00:22:39,084
The miscarriage.

328
00:22:44,463 --> 00:22:46,398
You never talked about it, so...

329
00:22:47,233 --> 00:22:49,793
I never talked about it.
Didn't wanna hurt you.

330
00:22:51,537 --> 00:22:53,802
But did you not talk about it...

331
00:22:54,573 --> 00:22:56,701
because you just
weren't thinking about it?

332
00:22:56,775 --> 00:22:58,300
What are all these questions for?

333
00:22:59,612 --> 00:23:01,945
I thought we were carrying the load...

334
00:23:02,047 --> 00:23:04,642
together, knowing how each other felt.

335
00:23:05,885 --> 00:23:07,478
This isn't about us.

336
00:23:08,787 --> 00:23:10,983
This is just a medical condition.

337
00:23:15,294 --> 00:23:16,990
If I died, would you care?

338
00:23:21,233 --> 00:23:23,395
Would you miss me? Or, uh...

339
00:23:23,469 --> 00:23:24,732
would you just...

340
00:23:25,704 --> 00:23:26,763
move on?

341
00:23:29,408 --> 00:23:31,604
Would you want me to be miserable?

342
00:23:31,710 --> 00:23:34,441
- I want it to matter.
- Of course it matters.

343
00:23:36,448 --> 00:23:37,973
You know I love you.

344
00:23:42,021 --> 00:23:43,489
Jonas...

345
00:23:44,223 --> 00:23:45,223
Maybe...

346
00:23:46,926 --> 00:23:48,861
you think it's love, but...

347
00:23:49,094 --> 00:23:51,586
it's like the pain.
It just doesn't go that deep.

348
00:23:51,664 --> 00:23:53,599
Isn't it possible for me to love you

349
00:23:53,666 --> 00:23:55,532
without it being
all wrapped up in suffering?

350
00:23:55,634 --> 00:23:57,535
But that's how it works.

351
00:23:59,838 --> 00:24:01,329
When you lose someone...

352
00:24:01,974 --> 00:24:04,842
it shouldn't be like your hand,
it should ache.

353
00:24:08,547 --> 00:24:10,015
That's right, isn't it?

354
00:24:10,783 --> 00:24:13,947
That's what loss feels like.

355
00:24:25,497 --> 00:24:27,398
I need to get away for a while.

356
00:24:28,701 --> 00:24:29,999
I'm sorry.

357
00:24:36,375 --> 00:24:40,836
Next, we're going to test you for
autoimmune hepatitis and fatty liver.

358
00:24:40,913 --> 00:24:43,883
Those are diseases
whose symptoms overlap yours.

359
00:24:43,983 --> 00:24:47,249
They might have been masked by
your idiopathic portal hypertension.

360
00:24:49,488 --> 00:24:52,515
Nurse Villanueva, welcome,
but you know I'm not gonna touch that.

361
00:24:52,591 --> 00:24:55,356
The dietician ordered it,
and I'm required to bring it.

362
00:24:56,862 --> 00:25:00,924
What are you eating
if you're refusing hospital food?

363
00:25:01,033 --> 00:25:02,501
Uh...

364
00:25:02,568 --> 00:25:05,697
Eighty grams of protein a day.
Kale, baby greens.

365
00:25:05,804 --> 00:25:06,828
Hey.

366
00:25:09,875 --> 00:25:11,741
"Leopard Spring."

367
00:25:12,811 --> 00:25:15,371
Jen, Dex, you mind stepping out?

368
00:25:22,054 --> 00:25:23,317
It's Chinese herbs.

369
00:25:23,422 --> 00:25:27,359
To make you feel younger,
more energetic, more virile.

370
00:25:27,559 --> 00:25:29,084
You don't feel virile?

371
00:25:29,194 --> 00:25:31,959
Of course, but there's nothing wrong
with feeling more virile.

372
00:25:32,097 --> 00:25:33,588
I need strength for the fight.

373
00:25:37,369 --> 00:25:39,861
You're not talking.
Is there a problem?

374
00:25:42,274 --> 00:25:44,539
No, these herbs are harmless.

375
00:25:44,610 --> 00:25:47,444
- You asked about my virility.
- I was curious.

376
00:25:47,880 --> 00:25:51,647
We're going to test you for
autoimmune hepatitis and fatty liver.

377
00:25:54,486 --> 00:25:56,751
- What's up?
- I tested a patient

378
00:25:56,855 --> 00:25:59,620
for autoimmune
hepatitis and fatty liver.

379
00:25:59,725 --> 00:26:01,318
What's up with you?

380
00:26:01,427 --> 00:26:03,623
Our patient decided
to take the drugs.

381
00:26:03,962 --> 00:26:06,955
Because a husband walking out
can make an impression

382
00:26:07,066 --> 00:26:09,126
even on a woman
who feels no pain.

383
00:26:11,570 --> 00:26:15,063
- It's a lot of paperwork for two tests.
- They were negative.

384
00:26:15,140 --> 00:26:17,075
I thought I might find something

385
00:26:17,142 --> 00:26:19,941
in his mother's old records
that could help,

386
00:26:20,012 --> 00:26:22,777
but, no, her case was straightforward.

387
00:26:22,881 --> 00:26:24,941
His parents were both alcoholics,

388
00:26:25,017 --> 00:26:27,748
but her liver was already
weakened by her condition.

389
00:26:28,120 --> 00:26:29,748
Parents both alcoholics?

390
00:26:29,822 --> 00:26:32,986
No wonder he thinks people in authority
like to deny the truth.

391
00:26:33,258 --> 00:26:37,992
He's grown up now, Claire.
No longer in that position.

392
00:26:39,298 --> 00:26:42,029
There's still plenty of lying
going on in the world.

393
00:26:42,134 --> 00:26:43,625
That's not a situation you outgrow.

394
00:26:45,804 --> 00:26:49,206
Yes, there is a lot of lying.

395
00:26:55,681 --> 00:26:59,345
Want to hear my theories?
Fight with your mother is number one.

396
00:26:59,451 --> 00:27:01,818
You're debating
whether to throw her out.

397
00:27:03,188 --> 00:27:04,554
This explains what?

398
00:27:04,656 --> 00:27:08,684
Why the compassionate Doctor Browne
envies a woman who feels no pain.

399
00:27:09,428 --> 00:27:11,192
You're miserable, torn,

400
00:27:11,296 --> 00:27:14,460
you don't know what to do
to make your pain go away.

401
00:27:17,202 --> 00:27:21,435
Want to hear my theory?
People that aren't you are doing great...

402
00:27:21,507 --> 00:27:25,137
so you're looking for a toy to break,
a pet you can torture.

403
00:27:35,454 --> 00:27:36,854
- Is she in pain?
- No.

404
00:27:36,955 --> 00:27:39,186
- What are her vitals?
- Vitals are fine.

405
00:27:39,258 --> 00:27:42,854
- Then how can she be in crisis?
- I don't know, but she is.

406
00:27:47,065 --> 00:27:48,397
Lily?

407
00:27:49,468 --> 00:27:50,561
Are you okay?

408
00:27:53,005 --> 00:27:54,005
Lily?

409
00:28:00,712 --> 00:28:03,341
I never noticed how
ugly the walls are.

410
00:28:15,727 --> 00:28:17,958
I've discovered the cause
of your liver problem.

411
00:28:18,063 --> 00:28:20,396
Really? Fatty liver? Autoimmune?

412
00:28:20,499 --> 00:28:23,958
- I've never had symptoms of...
- No, you were being poisoned.

413
00:28:24,703 --> 00:28:27,605
What? Who? Do you know who? How?

414
00:28:28,941 --> 00:28:33,106
I thought maybe the dose of herbs
listed on the bottle was wrong...

415
00:28:33,212 --> 00:28:36,546
- There's a toxic dose in there?
- No, there are no herbs at all in here.

416
00:28:36,615 --> 00:28:38,140
It contains sildenafil.

417
00:28:39,751 --> 00:28:45,213
It's the active element in Viagra.
It promotes blood flow in your penis.

418
00:28:49,261 --> 00:28:50,752
I know what it does.

419
00:28:51,163 --> 00:28:54,156
- They say it's natural herbs.
- They lied.

420
00:28:55,434 --> 00:28:58,029
Your idiopathic portal hypertension

421
00:28:58,103 --> 00:29:01,232
means your liver
is vulnerable to abuse.

422
00:29:01,306 --> 00:29:04,003
The amount of sildenafil in here
wouldn't kill most people,

423
00:29:04,109 --> 00:29:07,637
but if someone with pre-existing
liver issues took it every day...

424
00:29:08,480 --> 00:29:11,939
You were right.
You've been poisoning yourself.

425
00:29:16,955 --> 00:29:19,186
It's good news.

426
00:29:20,626 --> 00:29:23,596
Those communist bastards.

427
00:29:25,130 --> 00:29:27,793
I think they're based in San Pedro.

428
00:29:30,302 --> 00:29:31,634
Mr. Barstow.

429
00:29:33,071 --> 00:29:35,370
- Is Lily all right?
- She's on medication

430
00:29:35,474 --> 00:29:38,376
to reverse her pain-free condition,
but it's hit her hard.

431
00:29:38,710 --> 00:29:41,703
She's being wrung out by all
the negative thoughts and feelings

432
00:29:41,813 --> 00:29:44,078
the rest of us have built calluses against.

433
00:29:44,650 --> 00:29:47,779
But she made the right choice.
I mean, she needs this to be safe.

434
00:29:48,086 --> 00:29:49,850
I don't think she's doing this to be safe,

435
00:29:49,955 --> 00:29:52,049
I think she's doing this
because you walked out.

436
00:29:54,293 --> 00:29:55,293
Why?

437
00:29:56,395 --> 00:29:58,023
You were happy for years.

438
00:29:58,130 --> 00:30:01,032
Now you can't be happy
unless your wife changes?

439
00:30:02,834 --> 00:30:05,599
I want her to feel everything I feel.

440
00:30:06,972 --> 00:30:09,874
The love, the pain, everything.
Wouldn't you?

441
00:30:11,910 --> 00:30:14,709
The residents in this hospital
work long hours. Know why?

442
00:30:15,714 --> 00:30:18,980
The surgeons in charge worked
long hours when they were residents.

443
00:30:19,051 --> 00:30:21,680
They suffered, so we have to suffer.
It's human nature.

444
00:30:22,020 --> 00:30:23,740
- What does...
- For someone like your wife,

445
00:30:23,822 --> 00:30:27,122
so invulnerable, it's like she's
gotten away with something.

446
00:30:27,192 --> 00:30:28,421
It's hard not to resent her.

447
00:30:28,760 --> 00:30:31,355
Sure, we wanna cure her,
but how much of it

448
00:30:31,430 --> 00:30:33,763
is to give her a warning system,
and how much is because

449
00:30:33,899 --> 00:30:36,528
we wanna pull her down into hell
with the rest of us?

450
00:30:54,586 --> 00:30:55,610
Are you married now?

451
00:30:56,722 --> 00:30:58,782
No. I chickened out.

452
00:31:00,158 --> 00:31:03,686
Apparently, I don't like change.
Makes me very nervous.

453
00:31:04,696 --> 00:31:07,791
I'm not the easiest man in the world
to live with.

454
00:31:08,567 --> 00:31:10,399
My first wife made that very clear.

455
00:31:10,469 --> 00:31:13,962
It's true, you can be very irritating.

456
00:31:19,044 --> 00:31:21,104
You saying I shouldn't get married?

457
00:31:22,681 --> 00:31:25,116
Are you asking for my advice?

458
00:31:28,587 --> 00:31:29,587
Yes.

459
00:31:30,889 --> 00:31:34,826
You've never really asked before...

460
00:31:35,961 --> 00:31:40,626
and this is an important decision.
Your happiness depends on it.

461
00:31:42,234 --> 00:31:43,702
This is huge.

462
00:31:49,508 --> 00:31:50,508
Well?

463
00:31:52,411 --> 00:31:55,779
Oh. I don't have any advice.
I don't even understand the issue.

464
00:31:56,848 --> 00:31:59,079
I also don't understand why you asked

465
00:31:59,151 --> 00:32:01,347
when you've already
made up your mind.

466
00:32:01,486 --> 00:32:02,486
What?

467
00:32:03,155 --> 00:32:06,250
You usually call her your ex-wife.

468
00:32:06,324 --> 00:32:09,988
You just called her your first.
It implies a second.

469
00:32:20,839 --> 00:32:22,671
Why are you staring in your trunk?

470
00:32:22,974 --> 00:32:25,205
Something in here?
The answer to your problem?

471
00:32:28,647 --> 00:32:33,517
Yoga mat, gym bag, extra sneakers.

472
00:32:34,686 --> 00:32:38,487
Here's a little earthquake kit,
so sensible. Dirty towel.

473
00:32:39,157 --> 00:32:41,558
- Ooh, what's this?
- Put it back.

474
00:32:51,970 --> 00:32:52,970
It's my mom.

475
00:33:23,668 --> 00:33:25,068
Why are you jumping?

476
00:33:25,170 --> 00:33:27,537
I'm not jumping, I'm leaping.

477
00:33:29,207 --> 00:33:31,176
Come on. Come leap with me.

478
00:33:32,577 --> 00:33:35,206
We both can't leap on that thing.

479
00:33:35,313 --> 00:33:36,337
Oh!

480
00:33:37,682 --> 00:33:38,945
Are you okay?

481
00:33:41,753 --> 00:33:42,753
Never better.

482
00:33:43,555 --> 00:33:47,356
Will you leap with me to City Hall?

483
00:33:49,928 --> 00:33:51,021
Yes, I will.

484
00:33:52,030 --> 00:33:54,056
Also, I may have done
something to my ankle.

485
00:33:54,933 --> 00:33:58,597
- Do you want me to call someone?
<i>- Je ne regrette</i> nothing, baby.

486
00:34:06,611 --> 00:34:11,447
I left the champagne
because I was so ready for victory.

487
00:34:14,753 --> 00:34:17,621
Now I don't even know what
to do with the damn ashes.

488
00:34:18,623 --> 00:34:21,718
Leave them on a shelf in the closet
with the spare towels?

489
00:34:21,793 --> 00:34:23,659
Put them down the disposal?

490
00:34:23,762 --> 00:34:27,096
- What did she want done with them?
- It was stupid, I'm sure she was joking.

491
